From 052bd185e059c5256b6582f8846bd2de953e51b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Bohdan Chubuk <chbgdn@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 10:16:34 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 13/13] net: core: dev: Remove WARN_ON from
 dev_fill_bridge_path()

When the bridge floods a packet (unknown unicast, broadcast, multicast),
br_fill_forward_path may find an FDB entry that points back to the same
port. This triggers the WARN_ON_ONCE(last_dev == ctx->dev) check even
though it is a legitimate scenario.

Replace the WARN_ON with a silent return -1. The flow offload caller
will simply skip offloading this flow, which is the correct behavior.
---
 net/core/dev.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/net/core/dev.c
+++ b/net/core/dev.c
@@ -802,7 +802,7 @@ int dev_fill_bridge_path(struct net_devi
 	if (br_dev->netdev_ops->ndo_fill_forward_path(ctx, path) < 0)
 		return -1;
 
-	if (!ctx->dev || WARN_ON_ONCE(last_dev == ctx->dev))
+	if (!ctx->dev || last_dev == ctx->dev)
 		return -1;
 
 	return dev_fill_forward_path_common(ctx, stack);
